					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5245881#post-4344068</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5245881/scp-3230#post-4344068</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 29 Aug 2019 18:35:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>weiserthanyou</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2894859</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I haven't even finished the article and I've got to say, I was amazed to find the Penrose process being used in the containment procedures of an SCP. Kudos! And, of course, a slightly esoteric description of an Alcubierre drive. And Kerr-Newman black holes are an absolute win. +1 for the science alone!</p> <p>EDIT: Also, this is something pertinent to the contents of the scip: <a href="https://www.popularmechanics.com/space/deep-space/a28831167/how-to-build-a-wormhole/">Electrically charged black holes as wormholes</a><br /> Very nice to see someone even better versed in theoretical astrophysics than I am.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5245881#post-4314736</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5245881/scp-3230#post-4314736</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2019 20:01:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Quadruple Stuffed</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1417878</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Someone correct me if I'm wrong, but as long as the cosmic microwave background has a higher temperature than the Hawking radiation (which it should), the black hole will only be absorbing, and not emitting energy. Thus, no Hawking radiation coming from it should have been detected (unless this is meant to be part of its anomalous properties).</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
